---

<section class="guide-route-support" aria-label="Germany A1 route support">
  <h2>Quick answer</h2>
  <p>This guide is one step in the Germany A1 family reunion route. Use it to make the next decision, then verify the current requirement, accepted certificate, fee, date, and document rule with the responsible official source before booking or submitting anything.</p>

  <h2>Who this guide is for</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Germany family reunion applicants checking A1 language proof.</li>
    <li>Readers comparing Goethe A1, telc A1, booking, documents, preparation, or retake risk.</li>
    <li>People who want a practical checklist before using official pages.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Who this guide is not for</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Applicants who need legal advice on whether an exemption applies.</li>
    <li>Readers looking for guaranteed passing, leaked exam material, or copied real exam answers.</li>
    <li>People using a non-Germany route, such as university admission, work registration, or citizenship.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to verify officially</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Whether your exact family reunion case needs A1 proof.</li>
    <li>Which certificate and exam version your German mission or authority accepts.</li>
    <li>Local test center fee, date, ID rule, cancellation rule, result timing, and certificate delivery.</li>
    <li>Which original documents or copies are required for your exam day and visa file.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Common mistakes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Booking an exam before confirming the language requirement.</li>
    <li>Assuming fees, dates, and retake rules are the same in every country.</li>
    <li>Using unofficial preparation claims instead of official sample materials and original practice.</li>
    <li>Forgetting to leave time for results, certificate delivery, and a possible retake.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Step-by-step next action</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Start at the <a href="/germany-family-reunion-a1/">Germany A1 family reunion hub</a>.</li>
    <li>Confirm whether A1 applies in <a href="/guides/german-family-reunion-language-requirement/">German family reunion language requirement</a>.</li>
    <li>Choose an accepted proof using <a href="/guides/goethe-a1-germany-family-reunion/">Goethe A1 for Germany family reunion</a> and <a href="/guides/goethe-a1-vs-telc-a1/">Goethe A1 vs telc A1</a>.</li>
    <li>Check booking risk, documents, preparation, and retake timing before paying.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Related guides</h2>
  <div class="guide-related-grid">
    {coreGuides.map((guide) => (
      <a href={guide.href}>{guide.label}</a>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h2>Official sources</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.bamf.de/EN/Themen/MigrationAufenthalt/ZuwandererDrittstaaten/Familie/familie-node.html">BAMF family reunification</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www.goethe.de/en/spr/prf.html">Goethe-Institut German examinations</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www.telc.net/en/language-examinations/certificate-exams/german/start-german1-telc-german-a1/">telc Deutsch A1</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://www.auswaertiges-amt.de/en">German Federal Foreign Office</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Last updated</h2>
  <p>{updatedDate}. Official requirements, fees, dates, and accepted certificates can change after this page is updated.</p>

  <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
  <p>VisaLang is an exam-route navigation site, not a law firm, visa authority, test center, or exam provider. This page does not promise visa approval, exam availability, exam passing, or certificate acceptance.</p>
</section>
